default In July, Ofsted carried out 719 unscheduled inspections of providers that had been prompted by a complaint a 509 per cent increase since September 2012 when just 118 unscheduled inspections were carried out. During this time the number of providers given a lower rating following the complaint-driven inspection also rose significantly with 234 receiving a lower judgement in July, compared with 37 in September last year.
